title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J Kaiser Convention Center on 1988-02-14
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Apogee MiniMe (24bit/48k) -> Samplitude Professional v9.1.1 -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey, Feel Like A Stranger, Franklin's Tower, Walkin' Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, Cassidy

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station, Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue, Throwing Stones, Turn On Your Love Light, E: The Mighty Quinn

Mardi Gras Parade During Iko. w/ Batucaje percussion begins second setDr. John Opened* featuring Chinese dragon parade Chinese Symphony Orchestra Opened *W/ Hamza El Din *W/ Hamza El Din

reviews.review_text: Can't Re,view. Jaw, on floor. Proof of extraterestrial contact @ 6:00 in the Sampson jam.
- Yeah whatever: deadheads are gonna say what deadheads are gonna say. To a more impartial listener this is an OK show with a couple of nice spots, but overall it sounds like they're marking time.
